result.execSummary:
The defendant Anna M Luft was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: Crime against an Elderly or Disabled Person], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant, Anna M Luft appeared with Attorney James C. McLaughlin.  Attorney Thomas H Frost appeared for the State.  Court calls case and appearances.  Court speaks to the parties.  State speaks to the court re: the PSI and restitution. $869.50  Court speaks re: a recomendation.  Atty McL speaks to the court re: the PSI. The defendant speaks to the court.  

Sentencing--  3 years probation-- Conditions include. Absolute Sobriety. Not to consume any alcohol.  Not to consume or possess any controlled substances unless prescribed by a licensed doctor. AODA Assessment and any and all other condtions the DOC imposes along with behavioral health therapy.  

Stay and Impose 6 months jail. If the def. completes 100 hours of community service must be completed w/in the first 90 days of probation. Must complete some CS with the elderly population.  Jail time will be vacated if CS is completed.  

Restitution of $869.50 must be paid off in payments of $50.00/month starting immediately .  DNA Sample and surcharge.

State recites plea agreement PSI to be ordered and restitution no jail will be requested.  Atty McL agrees.  Court questions defendant as to plea questionnaire.   Defendant entered plea of no contest.  

Court finds defendant guilty - PSI ordered - no agent need appear  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 19, 2015 at 02:45 pm.
